column51: I have used AI tools (chatGPT) to both learn specific things about coding, and to optimise code that I wrote. I have found that it quite useful, and it seems to generate code that works. However, it seems to stumble on math, and sometimes points to resources on the web that do not actually exist. I think AI tools could help Stack Overflow in collecting, organizing, and summarizing information in a consise fashion. For example, maybe a question has been asked several times, and multiple different answers have been provided, with varying degrees of accuracy and effectiveness, maybe an AI tool can help analyze these answers and find a common pattern that points to the right solution. But then, I'm no expert on AI or coding, so this is just my two cents.
